message.content: cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE. This paper proposes a new strategy for named entity recognition (NER) using machine reading comprehension techniques, which falls under the sub-categories of natural language processing (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of informative prior knowledge, which could be relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and network embeddings (cs.NE).
